===Etymology===
From {{inh|ajp|ar|ـَة}}.

===Suffix===
{{ajp-suffix|head=ـة|tr=-e/-a/-t|g=f}}

# {{n-g|Ending of most feminine nouns in the singular}}
# {{n-g|Feminine suffix for nouns referring to people}}
# {{n-g|Feminine suffix for adjectives}}
# {{n-g|[[singulative|Singulative]] suffix from [[collective]] nouns (they become grammatically feminine)}}

====Usage notes====
* Nouns ending in {{m-self|ajp|ـة}} are not always feminine, it can also occur in broken plurals and rarely in masculine singular nouns.
* The pronunciation varies depending on the previous consonant. It might also vary by region, but generally the pronunciation is:
** “-a” ({{ajp-IPA|a<p:a>}}) after “throat” consonants (ʔ, ʕ, ḡ, h, ḥ, ḵ), e.g. {{m|ajp|لغة|tr=luḡa}}, {{m|ajp|منح|منيحة|tr=mnīḥa}}
** “-a” ({{ajp-IPA|a<p:ɑ>}}) after “emphatic” consonants (ḍ, q, r, ṣ, ṭ, ẓ), e.g. {{m|ajp|قصة|tr=ʾuṣṣa}}, {{m|ajp|مرة|tr=mara}}
** “-e” ({{ajp-IPA|a<p:ɛ~e>}}) after the remaining consonants and “r” in the ending “-īr”, e.g. {{m|ajp|غرفة|tr=ġurfe}}, {{m|ajp|كبير|كبيرة|tr=kbīre}}
** silent after a vowel “a”, which is then pronounced long and stressed, e.g. {{m|ajp|حياة|tr=ḥayā}}, {{m|ajp|صلاة|tr=ṣalā}}
* In the construct form (first noun of an [[idafa]]), the pronunciation is “-et” or “-at”, but the spelling remains unchanged.
*: {{uxi|ajp|بداية|tr=bidāy'''e'''|t=beginning}}
*: {{uxi|ajp|بداية القصة|tr=bidāy'''et''' il-ʾuṣṣa|t=the beginning of the story}}
* When a suffix is added, the spelling and pronunciation changes to {{m|ajp|ت|tr=t}}, with or without a preceding vowel, depending on the stress.
*: {{uxi|ajp|فرشة|tr=farš'''e'''|t=bed}}
*: {{uxi|ajp|فرشتي|tr=fárš'''t'''i|t=my bed}}
*: {{uxi|ajp|فرشتها|tr=farš'''ét'''ha|t=her bed}}

