#: {{m|hu|Amerika|t=America}} → {{m|hu|amerikai|amerika'''i'''|t=American}}
#: {{m|hu|város|t=city}} → {{m|hu|városi|város'''i'''|t=urban}}
#: {{m|hu|Freud|t=Freud}} → {{m|hu|freudi|freud'''i'''|t=Freudian}}
#: {{m|hu|[[az]] [[ablak]] [[alatt]]|t=under the window}} → {{m|hu|[[az]] [[ablak]] [[alatti|alatt'''i''']] [[szék]]|t=the chair under the window}}

=====Usage notes=====
* Final {{m|hu||-o}} and {{m|hu||-ö}} (which only occur in non-Hungarian words) change to {{m|hu||-ó}} and {{m|hu||-ő}}.<ref>{{R:hu:AkH2015|section=216}}</ref>
*: {{m|hu|Oslo}} → {{m|hu|oslói|osl'''ó'''i|Oslovian}}
*: {{m|hu|Malmö}} → {{m|hu|malmői|malm'''ő'''i|Malmö-based}}
*: {{m|hu||Victor Hugo}} → {{m|hu|Victor Hugó-i|Victor Hug'''ó'''-i|Hugolian, Hugonian, Hugoesque}}
* If the suffix {{m|hu||-i}} were to follow word-final {{m|hu||-i}}, only one is retained (so one needs to know the original form).<ref>{{R:hu:AkH2015|section=173}}</ref><ref>{{R:hu:AkH2015|section=215}}</ref>
*: {{m|hu|Helsinki}} → {{m|hu|helsinki|helsink'''i'''|Helsinkian}}
*: {{m|hu|Zamárdi|pos=a town in Somogy County, Hungary}} → {{m|hu|zamárdi|zamárd'''i'''|from Zamárdi|pos=in theory, it could also derive from a non-existent *Zamárd}}
* The other word-final short vowels ({{m|hu||a, e, u, ü}}) remain unchanged (just like long ones and consonants).
*: {{m|hu|Prága||Prague}} → {{m|hu|prágai|prág'''a'''i|Praguian}}
*: {{m|hu|Goethe}} → {{m|hu|goethei|goeth'''e'''i|Goethean}}
*: {{m|hu|Peru}} → {{m|hu|perui|per'''u'''i|Peruvian}}
*: {{m|hu|Öskü|pos=a village in Veszprém County, Hungary}} → {{m|hu|ösküi|ösk'''ü'''i|from Öskü}}
* The fact that word-final {{m|hu||a}} and {{m|hu||e}} remain short may carry distinction with the multiple-possession possessive form of a word that ends in {{m|hu||a}} and {{m|hu||e}}, e.g. {{m|hu|klinikai||clinical}} and {{m|hu|klinikái||his/her/its clinics}} or {{m|hu|megyei||county-level}} and {{m|hu|megyéi||his/her/its counties}},

