===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|se|smi-pro|*-ŋë}}. Cognate with {{cog|fi|-va}}.

====Suffix====
{{head|se|suffix|cat2=adjective-forming suffixes}}

# {{senseid|se|abundance}}{{n-g|Forms adjectives indicating an abundance of something.}}
#: {{suffixusex|se|geađgi|t1=stone|geađgái|t2=stony}}
#: {{suffixusex|se|vuodja|t1=fat|vuddjii|t2=rich in fat}}

=====Inflection=====
{{se-infl-noun-odd-ng|-j}}

=====Usage notes=====
{{U:se:suffgrade|x}}

Phonologically, the suffix is actually the consonant ''j'', and so it forms a diphthong with the final vowel of the base word's stem rather than replacing that vowel. Thus, the resulting word is essentially identical to the illative singular form. The noun declines as a contracted stem, with the inflectional stem lacking the ''-i''.

=====Derived terms=====
{{suffixsee|se|id=abundance}}

===Etymology 3===
{{rfe|se}}

====Suffix====
{{head|se|suffix|cat2=inflectional suffixes}}

# {{non-gloss definition|The ending of the illative singular case.}}

=====Usage notes=====
{{U:se:suffgrade|s}}

When possessive suffixes are attached, the suffix changes to the form {{m|se||-s-}} (for even-syllable stems) or {{m|se||-sa-}} (for odd-syllable stems).

