Middle Dutch {{m|dum|-ede}} was shortened to {{m|dum|-de}} in late Middle Dutch, and the suffix was devoiced to {{m|dum|-te}} according to the {{m|nl|'t kofschip}} rule. This voiceless variety was then taken to be the suffix proper and the voiced variety gradually fell out of use.

