===Etymology===
From {{inh|tr|ota|دا|tr=-de|t=locative suffix}}, from {{inh|tr|trk-pro|*-te|t=locative suffix}}, front vowel variant of {{m|trk-pro|*-ta}}. Cognate with {{cog|xqa|دا|tr=-dē|t=locative suffix}}, {{cog|otk|𐱅𐰀|ts=-te|t=locative suffix}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|tr|/de/}}

===Suffix===
{{tr-suffix|inflectional}}

# {{non-gloss definition|Used to form locative of nouns.}}
#: {{suffixusex|tr|köy|t1=village|köyde|t2=in/at village}}

====Usage notes====
* It’s used when the noun’s last vowel is a front vowel.
* It could be “{{l|tr|-da}}”, when the noun’s last vowel is a back vowel.
*: {{m|tr|okul}} → {{m|tr|okulda}}
* It could be “{{l|tr|-te}}”, when the noun’s final consonant is unvoiced.
*: {{m|tr|ofis}} → {{m|tr|ofiste}}
* It must be used with an [[apostrophe]] while forming a proper noun.
*: {{m|tr|Türkiye}} → {{m|tr|Türkiye'de|Türkiye’de}}

