# {{senseid|hu|possessive}} {{lb|hu|possessive suffix}} [[your]] ([[Appendix:Glossary#second person|second-person]] singular informal, single possession)
#: {{m|hu|hajó||boat}} → {{m|hu|hajód|a hajó'''d'''|'''your''' boat}}
#: {{m|hu|kocsi||car}} → {{m|hu|kocsid|a kocsi'''d'''|'''your''' car}}
#: {{m|hu|palota||palace}} → {{m|hu|palotád|a palotá'''d'''|'''your''' palace}}
#: {{m|hu|érme||coin}} → {{m|hu|érméd|az érmé'''d'''|'''your''' coin}}
# {{senseid|hu|personal}} {{lb|hu|personal suffix}} Used in the [[Appendix:Glossary#second person|second-person]] singular [[Appendix:Glossary#definite|definite]] forms of transitive verbs (in indicative present and past, subjunctive, and conditional moods).
#: {{m|hu|tudod}}, {{m|hu|kéred}}, {{m|hu|tudtad}}, {{m|hu|kérted}}, {{m|hu|tudjad}}, {{m|hu|kérjed}}, {{m|hu|tudnád}}, {{m|hu|kérnéd}}
## {{senseid|hu|subjunctive}} {{lb|hu|personal suffix|a subtype of the above}} When attached directly to a verb stem, it may be the combined form of a covert (∅) allophone of {{m|hu|-j||pos=subjunctive suffix}} and the regular suffix {{m|hu||-d}}, marking the short form of the second-person singular definite subjunctive.
##: {{m|hu|tudd}} (= {{m|hu|tudjad}}), {{m|hu|kérd#Etymology 2}} (= {{m|hu|kérjed}})
# {{senseid|hu|personal-inf}} {{lb|hu|personal suffix}} Second-person singular personal suffix in conjugated infinitives and in the declined and postposition forms of the second-person personal pronoun {{m|hu|te|t=you}}. Usually with linking vowels.
