==Proto-Germanic==

===Etymology===
From two sources, both reflecting earlier {{m|gem-pro||*-ōjaną}}:
* From {{inh|gem-pro|ine-pro|*-eh₂yéti}}, an innovated compound suffix from {{m|ine-pro|*-eh₂|pos=eh₂-stem noun suffix}} + {{m|ine-pro|*-yéti|pos=denominative suffix}}. These were originally formed as denominative verbs from ō-stem nouns. When attached to {{l|en|thematic}} (a-stem) nouns, the thematic vowel was also retained, but the resulting compound suffix {{m|ine-pro||*-eyé-}} became part of the first weak class instead.
* From {{inh|gem-pro|ine-pro|*-h₂yéti|*-(e)h₂yéti}}, an innovated compound suffix from {{m|ine-pro|*-h₂ti|*-(e)h₂ti|pos=factitive verb suffix}} which was originally athematic, but later extended with the thematic present suffix {{m|ine-pro|*-yéti}}.
Cognates include {{cog|la|-āre|pos=first conjugation}}, {{cog|grc|-άω|pos=contracted verb}}, {{cog|sa|-आयति|tr=-ā́yati}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|gem-pro|/ɔː.nɑ̃/}}

===Verb===
{{gem-verb}}

# {{non-gloss definition|Creates [[denominative]] verbs from nouns.}}
# {{non-gloss definition|Creates [[factitive]] verbs from adjectives.}}

====Inflection====
{{gem-conj-wk2|-}}

====Derived terms====
{{derivsee|Proto-Germanic class 2 weak verbs}}

====Descendants====
This class eventually became the dominant and most productive verb class in all daughter languages.

* {{desctree|gmw-pro|*-ōn}}
* {{desctree|non|-a|noalts=1}}
* {{desc|got|-𐍉𐌽}}

