#*: {{quote|ang|''Gangaþ tō Iosepe and '''dōþ''' swā hwæt swā hē ēow seċġe.''|Go to Joseph and '''do''' whatever he tells you.}}
#* '''c. 995''', [[w:Ælfric of Eynsham|Ælfric]], [https://archive.org/stream/grammatik00aelfuoft#page/n235 ''Extracts on Grammar in English'']
#*: {{quote|ang|''Ǣte þū tōdæġ? Iċ '''dyde'''.''|Did you eat today? I '''did'''.}}
#* '''c. 992''', [[w:Ælfric of Eynsham|Ælfric]], [https://books.google.com/books?id=J2cAAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA24&lpg=PA24 "Sermon on the Beginning of Creation"]
#*: {{quote|ang|''Þæt ċild wēox swā swā ōðru ċildru '''dōþ'''.''|The child grew as other children '''do'''.}}
#* '''late 10th century''', [[w:Ælfric of Eynsham|Ælfric]], ''[[w:Old English Hexateuch|the Old English Hexateuch]]'', [https://books.google.com/books?id=QrZUAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA30 Genesis 3:8]
#*: {{quote|ang|''Þā behȳdde Adam hine, and his wīf ēac swā '''dyde''', fram Godes ġesihte.''|Then Adam hid himself from God's sight, and his wife '''did''' so too.}}
# to [[make]], [[cause]]
#* '''c. 992''', [[w:Ælfric of Eynsham|Ælfric]], [https://books.google.com/books?id=2xobVW92JLcC&pg=PA468 "The Passion of St. Bartholomew the Apostle"]
#*: {{quote|ang|''Þū '''dydest''' mīnne brōðor his god forlǣtan.''|You '''made''' my brother renounce his god.}}
#* '''c. 990''', ''{{w|Wessex Gospels}}'', [https://archive.org/stream/dahalgangodspelo00thor#page/n13/mode/2up Matthew 3:3]
#*: {{quote|ang|''Ġeġearwiaþ Dryhtnes weġ, '''dōþ''' his sīðas rihte.''|Prepare the way of the Lord, '''make''' his paths straight.}}
#* '''c. 990''', ''{{w|Wessex Gospels}}'', [https://archive.org/stream/dahalgangodspelo00thor#page/n15/mode/2up Matthew 4:19]
#*: {{quote|ang|''Folgiaþ mē, and iċ '''dō''' þæt ġit bēoþ manna fisċeras.''|Follow me, and I'll '''make''' you fishers of people.}}
#* '''late 10th century''', [[w:Ælfric of Eynsham|Ælfric]], ''[[w:Old English Hexateuch|the Old English Hexateuch]]'', [https://books.google.com/books?id=QrZUAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA94 Genesis 42:36]
#*: {{quote|ang|''Þā cwæþ Iācōb heora fæder, "Bearnlēasne ġē habbaþ mē '''ġedōnne'''. Næbbe iċ Iōsēp and Simeon is on bendum; nū ġē nimaþ Beniamin æt mē."''|Then Jacob, their father, said, "You have '''made''' me childless. I don't have Joseph and Simeon is in chains; now you're taking Benjamin from me."}}
# to [[put]]
