==Irish==

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh-lite|ga|mga|ro-}}, from {{inh-lite|ga|sga|ro-}}, from {{inh|ga|cel-pro|*ɸro-}}, influenced by {{m-lite|sga|to-|do-}} of verbs like {{m-lite|sga|dobeir|do·beir|t=give}}, {{m-lite|sga|douccus|do·uccus|t=I have given}} (with early modern forms like {{m-lite|ga|do-bheirim|t=I give}}, {{m-lite|ga|do-ugas|t=I gave}}).

====Alternative forms====
* {{alter|ga|d’||used before vowels and lenited fh-}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|ga|/d̪ˠɔ/|/d̪ˠə/}}

====Particle====
{{head|ga|particle|triggers {{ga-mut-link|l}}}}

# {{lb|ga|Munster|literary}} {{n-g|prefixed before the preterite, imperfect and conditional forms of a verb}}
#: {{uxi|ga|'''do''' mhol sé|he praised}}

===Etymology 2===
Reanalysis of {{m-self|ga|do|t={{n-g|past tense marker}}}} and the early modern unstressed preverb {{m-lite|ga|do-}} of verbs like {{m-lite|ga|do-gheibhim|t=I get}}, {{m-lite|ga|do-chím|t=I see}} (and possibly also {{m-lite|ga|a-}} in {{m-lite|ga|a-tú|t=I am}}, {{m-lite|ga|a-deirim|t=I say}}) in relative clauses as a relative marker.

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|ga|/d̪ˠɔ/|/d̪ˠə/}}

====Particle====
{{head|ga|particle|triggers {{ga-mut-link|l}}}}

# {{lb|ga|Munster|literary}} {{n-g|relative marker (in direct relative clauses)}}
#: {{uxi|ga|an cailín '''do''' mholann sé|the girl that he praises}}

====Usage notes====
Before vowel sounds takes the form {{m|ga|d’}} and is often preceeded by the reduced form {{m|ga|a}}: {{m|ga|a dh’}}, {{m|ga|a d’}}:
# {{uxi|ga|an té a dh’éiríonn go moch, bíonn an rath air|he who raises early has the prosperity; the early bird catches the worm}}

