==Dutch==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|nl|dum|dat}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|that}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*þat}}, neuter form of {{m|gem-pro|*sa}}.

Cognate with {{cog|de|das}}, {{cog|en|that}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|nl|/dɑt/}}
* {{audio|nl|Nl-dat.ogg|audio}}
* {{hyphenation|nl|dat}}
* {{rhymes|nl|ɑt|s=1}}

===Determiner===
{{head|nl|determiner}}

# [[that]] (neuter); {{non-gloss definition|referring to a thing or a person further away.}}
#: {{ux|nl|'''dat''' huis|'''that''' house|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|nl|'''dat''' kind|'''that''' child|inline=1}}

====Inflection====
{{nl-decl-demonstrative determiner}}

====Derived terms====
* {{l|nl|datzelfde}}

====Descendants====
* {{desc|brc|dati}}
* {{desc|gmw-jdt|dāt}}
* {{desc|dcr|[[dat]], [[da]]}}

===Pronoun===
{{head|nl|pronoun|g=n}}

# {{lb|nl|demonstrative}} [[that]], that there
#: {{ux|nl|Wat is '''dat'''?|What is '''that'''?}}
# {{lb|nl|by extension|demonstrative|clipping of '''{{l|nl|datzelfde}}'''}} that same (thing), the aforementioned
#: {{ux|nl|–Voordat je weggaat, zet het afval buiten alsjeblieft!<br>–Okee, ik zal '''dat''' (doen).|–Before you leave, take the rubbish out please!<br>–Okay, I will do '''that'''.}}
# {{lb|nl|relative}} [[who]], [[which]], [[that]]
#: {{ux|nl|Ik ken een meisje '''dat''' dat kan.|I know a girl '''who''' can do that.}}
# {{lb|nl|exophoric}} [[that]], [[those]] {{q|regardless of gender and number}}
#: {{ux|nl|'''Dat''' is een man.|'''That''' is a man.}}
#: {{ux|nl|'''Dat''' zijn mannen.|'''Those''' are men.}}

====Usage notes====
This pronoun can combine with a preposition to form a [[pronominal adverb]]. When this occurs, it is changed into its adverbial/locative counterpart {{m|nl|daar}}. See also [[:Category:Dutch pronominal adverbs]].

A preceding comma may alter the meaning of a clause starting with a relative pronoun. Compare the following sentences:

* {{ux|nl|Het boek '''dat''' wit was, gaf ik terug.|I returned the book '''that''' was white. (The white book specifically, not another: specificative phrase)}}
* {{ux|nl|Het boek, '''dat''' wit was, gaf ik terug.|I returned the book, '''which''' was white. (The book happened to be white: explicative phrase)}}

====Descendants====
* {{desc|pey|dat}}
* {{desc|skw|dat}}

===Conjunction===
{{head|nl|conjunction}}

# [[that]] {{q|introducing a subordinate clause}}
#: {{ux|nl|Ik zag '''dat''' het goed was.|I saw '''that''' it was good.}}

====Usage notes====
* In Dutch the use of ''that'' is mandatory, with the following clause using the verb-final word order of subordinate clauses: ''Zij wist '''dat''' de lijkbidder te laat zou komen.'' (“She knew '''that''' the undertaker would arrive too late.”) A rare exception is found in some marginal slang contexts, that are often heavily influenced by English and where the conjunction is sometimes omitted.

====Derived terms====
{{der4|nl|doordat|nadat|omdat|opdat|totdat|voordat|zodat}}

====Descendants====
* {{desc|af|dat}}
* {{desc|dcr|dat}}

