===Etymology===
A regional form adopted into colloquial standard German. In western Germany from {{der|de|gmw-cfr|dat}}, from northern {{inh|de|gmh|dat}}, from northern {{inh|de|goh|that}}, {{m|goh|dat}}, an [[w:Old High German consonant shift|unshifted]] relict form possibly due to [[Frankish]] influence. In northern Germany from {{der|de|nds-de|dat}}, from {{der|de|gml|dat}}, from {{der|de|osx|that}}.

===Pronunciation===
