===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*bʰleh₃-}}
Spelled (until about 1830) and meaning {{m|en|flower}} in the sense of ''flour'' being the "finest portion of ground grain" (compare {{cog|fr|fleur de farine}}, {{m|fr|fine fleur}}). {{doublet|en|flower}}. Partially displaced native {{m|en|meal}}.

The U.S. standard of identity comes from [https://web.archive.org/web/20100722051913/http://www.access.gpo.gov/nara/cfr/waisidx_02/21cfr137_02.html 21CFR137.105].

