===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|sculle}}, {{m|enm|scolle}} (also {{m|enm|schulle}}, {{m|enm|scholle}}), probably from {{der|en|non|skalli||bald head, skull}}, itself probably related to {{cog|ang|sċealu||husk}}. Compare {{cog|sv|skalle}}, {{cog|no|skalle}}. <ref>http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/skull?s=t</ref>

Alternatively, perhaps from {{der|en|non|skoltr}}, {{m|non|skolptr|t=muzzle, snout}}, akin to {{cog|is|skoltur|t=jaw}}, dialectal {{cog|sv|skult}}, {{m|sv|skulle|t=dome, crown of the head, skull}}, {{cog|dum|scolle}}, {{m|dum|scholle}}, {{cog|gml|scholle}}, {{m|gml|schulle|t=clod, sod}}. Compare also {{noncog|goh|sciula}}, {{m|goh|skiula|t=skull}}.

====Alternative forms====
* {{l|en|scull}} {{qualifier|obsolete}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{enPR|skŭl}}, {{IPA|en|/skʌl/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-skull.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{homophones|en|scull}}
* {{rhymes|en|ʌl|s=1}}

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|anatomy}} The main [[bone]]s of the [[head]] considered as a unit; including the [[cranium]], facial bones, and [[mandible]].
#* '''1922''', {{w|Virginia Woolf}}, ''{{w|Jacob's Room}}'' Chapter 1
#*: He was about to roar when, lying among the black sticks and straw under the cliff, he saw a whole '''skull'''—perhaps a cow's '''skull''', a '''skull''', perhaps, with the teeth in it. Sobbing, but absent-mindedly, he ran farther and farther away until he held the '''skull''' in his arms.
# These bones as a symbol for [[death]]; [[death's-head]].
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} The [[mind]] or [[brain]].
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2006|author=Bart Yates|title=The Brothers Bishop|passage=My thoughts are flying around in my '''skull''' like fireflies in a jar, but all of a sudden I'm unbearably tired and can't stay awake.}}
# A [[crust]] formed on the [[ladle]], etc. by the partial cooling of [[molten]] [[metal]].
# The [[crown]] of the [[headpiece]] in [[armour]].
# {{lb|en|Scotland}} A [[shallow]] bow-handled [[basket]].

