===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*ters-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|test}}, {{m|enm|teste}}, from {{der|en|fro|test}}, {{m|fro|teste|t=an earthen vessel, especially a pot in which metals were tried}}, from {{der|en|la|testum|t=the lid of an earthen vessel, an earthen vessel, an earthen pot}}, from {{m|la|*terstus}}, past participle of the root {{m|la|*tersa||dry land}}. See [[terra]], [[thirst]].

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A [[challenge#Noun|challenge]], [[trial]].
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=2012|month=March-April| author=Colin Allen| title=Do I See What You See?| volume=100| issue=2| page=168| magazine={{w|American Scientist}}| url=http://www.americanscientist.org/bookshelf/pub/do-i-see-what-you-see| passage=Numerous experimental '''tests''' and other observations have been offered in favor of animal mind reading, and although many scientists are skeptical, others assert that humans are not the only species capable of representing what others do and don’t perceive and know.}}
# A [[cupel]] or cupelling hearth in which precious metals are melted for trial and refinement.
# {{lb|en|academia}} An [[examination]], given often during the academic [[term]].
# A [[session]] in which a product or piece of equipment is [[examine]]d under everyday or extreme conditions to [[evaluate]] its [[durability]], etc.
# {{lb|en|cricket|normally “[[Test]]”}} A [[Test match]].
# {{lb|en|marine biology}} The external [[calciferous]] shell, or [[endoskeleton]], of an [[echinoderm]], e.g. [[sand dollar|sand dollars]] and [[sea urchin|sea urchins]].[[Image:Sea urchin tests.jpg|thumb|right|Two sea urchin tests]]
# {{lb|en|botany}} [[testa|Testa]]; [[seed coat]].
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} [[judgment|Judgment]]; [[distinction]]; [[discrimination]].
#* {{RQ:Dryden Aureng-zebe|passage=Who would excel, when few can make a '''test''' / Betwixt indifferent writing and the best?}}

